    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fortified sanctuaries used as a refuge in times of war, situated on hilltops in eastern Kenya among the Mijikenda and related peoples. Many kayas are regarded as sacred sites. a primary division of a building’s elevation</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
